We can use the strlen() function to get the length of a string.
For eg.

char s[] = "hello";
int a = strlen(s); // a now stores the length of s.
Task
Write a program which does the following

Create a variable txt and assign it the text "NumeroTres"
Use the strlen() function to output to the console the number of characters in txt Output Format The length of the word is: {length}

Sol.:-
#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>

int main()  {
    
    char txt[] = "NumeroTres";
    printf("The length of the word is: %d",strlen(txt));
    
    return 0;
    
}
